Gayne Whitman https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gayne_Whitman 0 Gayne Whitman (March 19, 1890 – August 31, 1958) was an American radio and film actor. He appeared in 213 films between 1904 and 1957. In some early films he was credited under his birth name, Alfred Vosburgh. He was born in Chicago, Illinois. On radio, he played the title role in Chandu the Magician and was an announcer on other programs. Gayne_Whitman ( March_19_,_1890 – August_31_,_1958 ) was an_American_radio_and_film_actor .
